WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.478 --> 00:00:12.978
(Gate rumbling. chains rattling)

2
00:00:42.309 --> 00:00:45.160
         (Horse snorts)

3
00:00:57.324 --> 00:00:59.641
   (Rumbling. chain rattling)

4
00:01:40.450 --> 00:01:42.584
        (Wind whistling)

5
00:01:56.867 --> 00:01:59.033
           EASY. BOY.
           (Grunts)

6
00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:02.463
        (Horse whinnies)

7
00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:14.209
   Man: WHAT DO YOU EXPECT ?
   THEY'RE SAVAGES.

8
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:16.711
   ONE LOT STEALS A GOAT FROM
   ANOTHER LOT.

9
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:19.180
 BEFORE YOU KNOW IT THEY'RE
 RIPPING EACH OTHER TO PIECES.

10
00:03:19.249 --> 00:03:21.783
I'VE NEVER SEEN WILDLINGS
DO A THING LIKE THIS.

11
00:03:21.851 --> 00:03:24.085
I NEVER SEEN A THING LIKE THIS.
NOT EVER IN MY LIFE.

12
00:03:24.154 --> 00:03:26.354
(Horse snorts)
         HOW CLOSE DID YOU GET ?

13
00:03:26.423 --> 00:03:30.641
CLOSE AS ANY MAN WOULD.
WE SHOULD HEAD BACK TO THE WALL.

14
00:03:32.496 --> 00:03:33.995
DO THE DEAD FRIGHTEN YOU ?

15
00:03:34.063 --> 00:03:36.264
         OUR ORDERS WERE
         TO TRACK THE WILDLINGS.

16
00:03:36.332 --> 00:03:39.600
     WE TRACKED THEM. THEY WON'T
     TROUBLE US NO MORE.

17
00:03:39.670 --> 00:03:42.671
YOU DON'T THINK HE'LL ASK US
HOW THEY DIED ?

18
00:03:44.307 --> 00:03:46.007
GET BACK ON YOUR HORSE.

19
00:03:47.711 --> 00:03:49.610
        (Sighs. mutters)

20
00:03:50.847 --> 00:03:53.381
WHATEVER DID IT TO THEM
COULD DO IT TO US.

21
00:03:53.450 --> 00:03:55.934
THEY EVEN KILLED
THE CHILDREN.

22
00:03:56.003 --> 00:03:59.321
             IT'S A GOOD THING
             WE'RE NOT CHILDREN.

23
00:03:59.389 --> 00:04:02.223
     YOU WANT TO RUN AWAY SOUTH.
     RUN AWAY.

24
00:04:02.292 --> 00:04:05.293
       OF COURSE. THEY WILL
       BEHEAD YOU AS A DESERTER.

25
00:04:05.362 --> 00:04:07.362
     IF I DON'T CATCH YOU FIRST.

26
00:04:09.850 --> 00:04:12.200
         GET BACK ON YOUR HORSE.

27
00:04:12.269 --> 00:04:14.035
           I WON'T SAY IT AGAIN.

28
00:04:32.255 --> 00:04:34.255
      (Shrill animal call)

29
00:04:45.702 --> 00:04:48.887
      YOUR DEAD MEN SEEM
      TO HAVE MOVED CAMP.

30
00:04:48.955 --> 00:04:50.622
        THEY WERE HERE.

31
00:04:53.994 --> 00:04:55.727
            SEE WHERE THEY WENT.

32
00:05:11.061 --> 00:05:13.628
    (Echoing creature cries)

33
00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:43.975
          WHAT IS IT ?

34
00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:47.479
             IT'S--

35
00:05:47.547 --> 00:05:49.297
            (Cracking. creaking)

36
00:05:51.752 --> 00:05:53.869
        (Distant scream)

37
00:05:53.937 --> 00:05:56.170
       (Horses neighing)

38
00:05:56.239 --> 00:05:57.923
       (Galloping hooves)

39
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:29.554
           (Snarling)

40
00:06:29.623 --> 00:06:31.723
          (Chittering)

41
00:06:40.150 --> 00:06:42.017
           (Coughing)

42
00:06:44.021 --> 00:06:45.854
           (Coughing)

43
00:06:45.939 --> 00:06:48.006
           (Panting)

44
00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:50.841
      (Labored breathing)

45
00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:52.860
           (Snarling)

46
00:06:55.215 --> 00:06:56.530
            (Gasps)

47
00:07:01.738 --> 00:07:03.254
          (Crackling)

48
00:07:11.781 --> 00:07:13.648
          (Chittering)

49
00:09:00.974 --> 00:09:03.041
       (Galloping hooves)

50
00:09:43.783 --> 00:09:44.749
            (Stamps)

51
00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:51.572
       GO ON. FATHER'S WATCHING.

52
00:09:54.177 --> 00:09:55.809
AND YOUR MOTHER.

53
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:05.503
     FINE WORK. AS ALWAYS.
     WELL DONE.

54
00:10:05.572 --> 00:10:07.271
THANK YOU.

55
00:10:07.340 --> 00:10:11.242
I LOVE THE DETAIL THAT YOU'VE
MANAGED TO GET IN THESE CORNERS.

56
00:10:11.311 --> 00:10:13.177
        QUITE BEAUTIFUL.

57
00:10:13.246 --> 00:10:15.179
                 THE STITCHING--

58
00:10:15.248 --> 00:10:17.482
     OH. NO. NO. NO.
     THIS STITCH IS VERY--

59
00:10:17.550 --> 00:10:19.084
(Arrows impacting. men laughing)

60
00:10:19.152 --> 00:10:22.286
        IT'S BEAUTIFUL.
                      THANK YOU.

61
00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.228
       (Arrow impacting)

62
00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:36.217
(Sighs)
           (Laughing)

63
00:10:36.286 --> 00:10:40.037
    AND WHICH ONE OF YOU
    WAS A MARKSMAN AT TEN ?

64
00:10:40.090 --> 00:10:42.107
     KEEP PRACTICING. BRAN.

65
00:10:43.727 --> 00:10:45.760
             GO ON.

66
00:10:45.846 --> 00:10:48.112
     DON'T THINK TOO MUCH. BRAN.

67
00:10:50.951 --> 00:10:52.951
      RELAX YOUR BOW ARM.

68
00:11:02.195 --> 00:11:05.146
         (Men laughing)

69
00:11:05.215 --> 00:11:08.266
         QUICK. BRAN !
         FASTER.

70
00:11:08.335 --> 00:11:09.867
LORD STARK !

71
00:11:12.355 --> 00:11:14.389
MY LADY.

72
00:11:14.457 --> 00:11:16.724
A GUARDSMAN JUST RODE IN
FROM THE HILLS.

73
00:11:16.793 --> 00:11:19.744
THEY'VE CAPTURED A DESERTER
FROM THE NIGHT'S WATCH.

74
00:11:23.083 --> 00:11:25.283
    GET THE LADS
    TO SADDLE THEIR HORSES.

75
00:11:25.352 --> 00:11:27.334
                DO YOU HAVE TO ?

76
00:11:27.403 --> 00:11:29.554
     HE SWORE AN OATH. CAT.

77
00:11:29.622 --> 00:11:32.590
LAW IS LAW. MY LADY.

78
00:11:32.659 --> 00:11:34.542
   TELL BRAN HE'S COMING TOO.

79
00:11:36.613 --> 00:11:38.279
                            NED.

80
00:11:38.365 --> 00:11:40.699
             TEN IS TOO YOUNG
             TO SEE SUCH THINGS.

81
00:11:40.767 --> 00:11:43.000
HE WON'T BE A BOY FOREVER.

82
00:11:44.321 --> 00:11:47.071
AND WINTER IS COMING.

83
00:12:05.125 --> 00:12:08.442
     GOOD LAD. GO RUN BACK
     AND GET THE REST.

84
00:12:13.467 --> 00:12:15.082
         WHITE WALKERS.

85
00:12:15.152 --> 00:12:17.952
    I SAW THE WHITE WALKERS.

86
00:12:18.021 --> 00:12:19.954
         WHITE WALKERS.

87
00:12:20.023 --> 00:12:23.124
 THE WHITE WALKERS. I SAW THEM.

88
00:12:23.193 --> 00:12:24.925
           (Exhales)

89
00:12:31.868 --> 00:12:34.636
    I KNOW I BROKE MY OATH.

90
00:12:34.704 --> 00:12:37.021
   AND I KNOW I'M A DESERTER.

91
00:12:37.090 --> 00:12:40.841
I SHOULD HAVE GONE BACK TO
THE WALL AND WARNED THEM. BUT...

92
00:12:40.910 --> 00:12:42.976
I SAW WHAT I SAW.

93
00:12:43.045 --> 00:12:44.479
I SAW THE WHITE WALKERS.

94
00:12:46.550 --> 00:12:48.266
      PEOPLE NEED TO KNOW.

95
00:12:50.553 --> 00:12:52.420
      IF YOU CAN GET WORD
      TO MY FAMILY...

96
00:12:52.488 --> 00:12:54.855
    TELL THEM I'M NO COWARD.

97
00:12:54.924 --> 00:12:56.707
      TELL THEM I'M SORRY.

98
00:13:13.893 --> 00:13:15.443
  (Whispers) FORGIVE ME. LORD.

99
00:13:19.966 --> 00:13:22.199
    IN THE NAME OF ROBERT
    OF THE HOUSE BARATHEON.

100
00:13:22.268 --> 00:13:24.252
    THE FIRST OF HIS NAME...
                DON'T LOOK AWAY.

101
00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:25.987
     ...KING OF THE ANDALS
     AND THE FIRST MEN...

102
00:13:26.055 --> 00:13:27.221
     FATHER WILL KNOW IF YOU DO.

103
00:13:27.290 --> 00:13:28.906
  ..LORD OF THE SEVEN KINGDOMS

104
00:13:28.975 --> 00:13:30.675
  AND PROTECTOR OF THE REALM.

105
00:13:30.743 --> 00:13:33.694
 I. EDDARD OF THE HOUSE STARK.

106
00:13:33.763 --> 00:13:36.363
    LORD OF WINTERFELL
    AND WARDEN OF THE NORTH.

107
00:13:36.432 --> 00:13:38.800
            SENTENCE YOU TO DIE.

108
00:13:53.683 --> 00:13:55.216
                   YOU DID WELL.

109
00:14:23.546 --> 00:14:25.045
YOU UNDERSTAND WHY I DID IT ?

110
00:14:25.115 --> 00:14:27.098
  JON SAID HE WAS A DESERTER.

111
00:14:27.150 --> 00:14:29.717
BUT DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I HAD TO KILL HIM ?

112
00:14:29.786 --> 00:14:31.319
      "OUR WAY IS THE OLD WAY" ?

113
00:14:33.056 --> 00:14:37.692
THE MAN WHO PASSES THE SENTENCE
SHOULD SWING THE SWORD.

114
00:14:37.761 --> 00:14:40.077
             IS IT TRUE HE SAW
             THE WHITE WALKERS ?

115
00:14:42.215 --> 00:14:46.250
THE WHITE WALKERS HAVE BEEN GONE
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

116
00:14:46.319 --> 00:14:47.818
       SO HE WAS LYING ?

117
00:14:52.325 --> 00:14:54.558
A MADMAN SEES WHAT HE SEES.

118
00:15:20.620 --> 00:15:22.319
WHAT IS IT ?

119
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:26.257
                 MOUNTAIN LION ?

120
00:15:27.961 --> 00:15:30.828
  THERE ARE NO MOUNTAIN LIONS
  IN THESE WOODS.

121
00:15:57.540 --> 00:15:59.673
          (Pup whines)

122
00:16:16.459 --> 00:16:18.392
                   IT'S A FREAK.

123
00:16:19.629 --> 00:16:21.612
                IT'S A DIREWOLF.

124
00:16:30.173 --> 00:16:32.256
                TOUGH OLD BEAST.

125
00:16:34.710 --> 00:16:37.628
    THERE ARE NO DIREWOLVES
    SOUTH OF THE WALL.

126
00:16:37.697 --> 00:16:40.531
      NOW THERE ARE FIVE.

127
00:16:40.599 --> 00:16:42.383
           YOU WANT TO HOLD IT ?

128
00:16:43.786 --> 00:16:45.753
         (Pup whimpers)

129
00:16:46.823 --> 00:16:48.355
   Bran: WHERE WILL THEY GO ?

130
00:16:48.425 --> 00:16:50.241
      THEIR MOTHER'S DEAD.

131
00:16:50.293 --> 00:16:51.892
THEY DON'T BELONG
DOWN HERE.

132
00:16:51.961 --> 00:16:55.796
BETTER A QUICK DEATH. THEY WON'T
LAST WITHOUT THEIR MOTHER.

133
00:16:55.882 --> 00:16:57.965
RIGHT. GIVE IT HERE.
              NO !

134
00:16:58.051 --> 00:16:59.700
           (Whimpers)
PUT AWAY YOUR BLADE.

135
00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:02.769
I TAKE ORDERS FROM YOUR FATHER.
NOT YOU.
        PLEASE. FATHER !

136
00:17:02.838 --> 00:17:04.672
        I'M SORRY. BRAN.

137
00:17:04.740 --> 00:17:06.607
                    LORD STARK ?

138
00:17:07.594 --> 00:17:10.394
            THERE ARE FIVE PUPS.

139
00:17:10.463 --> 00:17:12.630
   ONE FOR EACH OF THE STARK
   CHILDREN.

140
00:17:12.699 --> 00:17:16.500
(Pup cries)
    THE DIREWOLF IS
    THE SIGIL OF YOUR HOUSE.

141
00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:18.686
   THEY WERE MEANT TO HAVE THEM.

142
00:17:24.026 --> 00:17:26.243
      YOU WILL TRAIN THEM
      YOURSELVES.

143
00:17:26.312 --> 00:17:28.279
 YOU WILL FEED THEM YOURSELVES.

144
00:17:28.348 --> 00:17:31.982
 AND IF THEY DIE.
 YOU WILL BURY THEM YOURSELVES.

145
00:17:39.809 --> 00:17:42.359
        WHAT ABOUT YOU ?

146
00:17:42.428 --> 00:17:44.161
        I'M NOT A STARK.

147
00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:45.963
                         GET ON.

148
00:17:53.288 --> 00:17:55.489
          (Whimpering)

149
00:17:56.359 --> 00:17:58.359
          WHAT IS IT ?

150
00:18:02.015 --> 00:18:06.451
         THE RUNT OF THE LITTER.
         THAT ONE'S YOURS. SNOW.

151
00:18:14.527 --> 00:18:17.077
        (Bells tolling)

152
00:19:05.711 --> 00:19:10.081
  AS YOUR BROTHER. I FEEL
  IT'S MY DUTY TO WARN YOU...

153
00:19:10.149 --> 00:19:12.165
             YOU WORRY TOO MUCH.

154
00:19:12.234 --> 00:19:13.951
          IT'S STARTING TO SHOW.

155
00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:16.804
AND YOU NEVER WORRY
ABOUT ANYTHING.

156
00:19:16.872 --> 00:19:20.891
WHEN WE WERE SEVEN AND YOU
JUMPED OFF THE CLIFFS
AT CASTERLY ROCK.

157
00:19:20.944 --> 00:19:25.379
100-FOOT DROP INTO THE WATER--
YOU WERE NEVER AFRAID.

158
00:19:25.448 --> 00:19:28.132
            THERE WAS NOTHING TO
            BE AFRAID OF UNTIL
            YOU TOLD FATHER.

159
00:19:28.201 --> 00:19:32.369
     (Mimics) "WE'RE LANNISTERS.
     LANNISTERS DON'T ACT
     LIKE FOOLS."

160
00:19:34.207 --> 00:19:37.675
WHAT IF JON ARRYN TOLD SOMEONE ?
         BUT WHO WOULD HE TELL ?

161
00:19:39.094 --> 00:19:40.527
MY HUSBAND.

162
00:19:40.596 --> 00:19:42.779
IF HE TOLD THE KING.
BOTH OUR HEADS WOULD BE SKEWERED

163
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:45.599
       ON THE CITY GATES BY NOW.

164
00:19:45.668 --> 00:19:49.603
  WHATEVER JON ARRYN KNEW OR
  DIDN'T KNOW. IT DIED WITH HIM.

165
00:19:49.672 --> 00:19:51.572
         AND ROBERT WILL CHOOSE
         A NEW HAND OF THE KING.

166
00:19:51.641 --> 00:19:55.543
    SOMEONE TO DO HIS JOB
    WHILE HE'S OFF FUCKING BOARS
    AND HUNTING WHORES.

167
00:19:55.611 --> 00:19:57.428
 OR IS IT THE OTHER WAY AROUND ?

168
00:19:58.565 --> 00:20:00.964
      AND LIFE WILL GO ON.

169
00:20:01.034 --> 00:20:03.200
YOU SHOULD BE
THE HAND OF THE KING.

170
00:20:04.553 --> 00:20:06.353
       THAT'S AN HONOR
       I CAN DO WITHOUT.

171
00:20:06.422 --> 00:20:08.122
    THEIR DAYS ARE TOO LONG.

172
00:20:08.190 --> 00:20:10.691
   THEIR LIVES ARE TOO SHORT.

173
00:20:14.263 --> 00:20:16.380
       (Thunder rumbles)

174
00:20:22.638 --> 00:20:23.587
             (Caws)

175
00:20:38.071 --> 00:20:39.836
        (Birds chirping)

176
00:20:49.398 --> 00:20:50.664
ALL THESE YEARS.

177
00:20:50.733 --> 00:20:54.034
AND I STILL FEEL LIKE
AN OUTSIDER WHEN I COME HERE.

178
00:20:55.705 --> 00:20:58.556
              YOU HAVE FIVE
              NORTHERN CHILDREN.

179
00:20:58.624 --> 00:21:00.958
         YOU'RE NOT AN OUTSIDER.

180
00:21:01.026 --> 00:21:04.712
I WONDER IF
THE OLD GODS AGREE.

181
00:21:04.797 --> 00:21:07.197
             IT'S YOUR GODS
             WITH ALL THE RULES.

182
00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:16.790
I AM SO SORRY. MY LOVE.

183
00:21:16.859 --> 00:21:18.425
            TELL ME.

184
00:21:18.511 --> 00:21:20.978
THERE WAS A RAVEN
FROM KING'S LANDING.

185
00:21:22.648 --> 00:21:24.231
JON ARRYN IS DEAD.

186
00:21:24.317 --> 00:21:26.450
A FEVER TOOK HIM.

187
00:21:29.755 --> 00:21:33.040
I KNOW HE WAS LIKE
A FATHER TO YOU.

188
00:21:34.977 --> 00:21:38.095
          YOUR SISTER. THE BOY ?
THEY BOTH HAVE THEIR HEALTH.

189
00:21:38.164 --> 00:21:39.964
GODS BE GOOD.

190
00:21:50.393 --> 00:21:52.777
THE RAVEN BROUGHT
MORE NEWS.

191
00:21:53.879 --> 00:21:57.248
THE KING RIDES
FOR WINTERFELL...

192
00:21:57.316 --> 00:22:00.951
WITH THE QUEEN
AND ALL THE REST OF THEM.

193
00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:04.955
               IF HE'S COMING
               THIS FAR NORTH...

194
00:22:05.024 --> 00:22:06.974
          THERE'S ONLY ONE THING
          HE'S AFTER.

195
00:22:07.042 --> 00:22:10.060
YOU CAN ALWAYS SAY NO. NED.

196
00:22:18.804 --> 00:22:22.539
  Catelyn:
  WE'LL NEED PLENTY OF CANDLES
  FOR LORD TYRION'S CHAMBER.

197
00:22:22.608 --> 00:22:26.443
I'M TOLD HE READS ALL NIGHT.
   I'M TOLD HE DRINKS ALL NIGHT.

198
00:22:26.512 --> 00:22:29.713
   HOW MUCH COULD HE POSSIBLY
   DRINK ? A MAN OF HIS...

199
00:22:29.782 --> 00:22:31.415
           STATURE ?

200
00:22:31.484 --> 00:22:34.418
 WE'VE BROUGHT UP EIGHT BARRELS
 OF ALE FROM THE CELLAR.

201
00:22:34.487 --> 00:22:35.753
PERHAPS WE'LL FIND OUT.

202
00:22:35.821 --> 00:22:37.921
           IN ANY CASE. CANDLES.

203
00:22:43.745 --> 00:22:46.713
WHY IS YOUR MOTHER SO DEAD SET
ON US GETTING PRETTY
FOR THE KING ?

204
00:22:46.782 --> 00:22:49.616
 IT'S FOR THE QUEEN. I BET. I
 HEAR SHE'S A SLEEK BIT OF MINK.

205
00:22:49.702 --> 00:22:51.801
  I HEAR THE PRINCE IS A RIGHT
  ROYAL PRICK.

206
00:22:51.871 --> 00:22:56.139
     THINK OF ALL THOSE SOUTHERN
     GIRLS HE GETS TO STAB
     WITH HIS RIGHT ROYAL PRICK.

207
00:22:57.243 --> 00:22:59.409
 GO ON. TOMMY. SHEAR HIM GOOD.

208
00:22:59.478 --> 00:23:01.845
 HE'S NEVER MET A GIRL HE LIKES
 BETTER THAN HIS OWN HAIR.

209
00:23:01.914 --> 00:23:04.164
           (Laughter)

210
00:23:38.784 --> 00:23:42.202
(Pup yaps)
   GODS. BUT THEY GROW FAST.

211
00:23:43.923 --> 00:23:45.439
BRANDON !

212
00:23:45.508 --> 00:23:48.575
    I SAW THE KING.
    HE'S GOT HUNDREDS OF PEOPLE.

213
00:23:48.644 --> 00:23:51.778
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I TOLD YOU ?
NO CLIMBING.

214
00:23:51.848 --> 00:23:55.232
   BUT HE'S COMING RIGHT NOW.
   DOWN OUR ROAD.

215
00:24:01.824 --> 00:24:04.341
I WANT YOU TO PROMISE ME.

216
00:24:04.393 --> 00:24:06.776
NO MORE CLIMBING.

217
00:24:10.866 --> 00:24:12.682
           I PROMISE.

218
00:24:14.253 --> 00:24:17.337
DO YOU KNOW WHAT ?
             WHAT ?

219
00:24:17.406 --> 00:24:19.706
YOU ALWAYS LOOK AT YOUR FEET
BEFORE YOU LIE.

220
00:24:19.792 --> 00:24:21.725
           (Chuckles)

221
00:24:21.794 --> 00:24:23.594
RUN AND FIND YOUR FATHER.

222
00:24:23.663 --> 00:24:25.579
TELL HIM THE KING IS CLOSE.

223
00:25:10.092 --> 00:25:13.593
    WHERE'S ARYA ?
    SANSA. WHERE'S YOUR SISTER ?

224
00:25:23.823 --> 00:25:26.022
             HEY. HEY. HEY. HEY.
              OH.

225
00:25:26.091 --> 00:25:28.792
              WHAT ARE YOU DOING
              WITH THAT ON ?

226
00:25:30.429 --> 00:25:32.496
             GO ON.
(Groans)

227
00:25:33.899 --> 00:25:35.465
Arya: MOVE !

228
00:25:53.218 --> 00:25:55.019
            (Neighs)

229
00:26:57.716 --> 00:26:59.532
                     YOUR GRACE.

230
00:27:04.089 --> 00:27:06.222
        YOU'VE GOT FAT.

231
00:27:12.397 --> 00:27:15.048
           (Laughter)

232
00:27:17.836 --> 00:27:19.987
          CAT !
                     YOUR GRACE.

233
00:27:23.492 --> 00:27:25.742
NINE YEARS.
WHY HAVEN'T I SEEN YOU ?

234
00:27:25.794 --> 00:27:27.110
WHERE THE HELL HAVE YOU BEEN ?

235
00:27:27.179 --> 00:27:29.379
     GUARDING THE NORTH FOR YOU.
     YOUR GRACE.

236
00:27:29.448 --> 00:27:31.849
   Ned: WINTERFELL IS YOURS.

237
00:27:34.536 --> 00:27:37.137
       WHERE'S THE IMP ?
              WILL YOU SHUT UP ?

238
00:27:37.206 --> 00:27:40.039
Robert: WHO HAVE WE HERE ?

239
00:27:40.108 --> 00:27:42.359
       YOU MUST BE ROBB.

240
00:27:44.396 --> 00:27:46.663
MY. YOU'RE A PRETTY ONE.

241
00:27:47.917 --> 00:27:49.849
         YOUR NAME IS ?

242
00:27:49.919 --> 00:27:52.469
             ARYA.

243
00:27:52.537 --> 00:27:55.172
   OH. SHOW US YOUR MUSCLES.

244
00:27:56.409 --> 00:27:58.642
(Chuckles) YOU'LL BE A SOLDIER.

245
00:28:01.614 --> 00:28:04.114
 Arya: THAT'S JAIME LANNISTER.
 THE QUEEN'S TWIN BROTHER.

246
00:28:04.182 --> 00:28:06.233
    Sansa: WOULD YOU PLEASE
    SHUT UP ?

247
00:28:15.861 --> 00:28:17.294
           MY QUEEN.

248
00:28:18.147 --> 00:28:19.780
           MY QUEEN.

249
00:28:19.865 --> 00:28:21.932
TAKE ME TO YOUR CRYPT.
I WANT TO PAY MY RESPECTS.

250
00:28:22.001 --> 00:28:24.250
 WE'VE BEEN RIDING FOR A MONTH.
 MY LOVE.

251
00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:25.985
   SURELY THE DEAD CAN WAIT.

252
00:28:26.072 --> 00:28:27.821
NED.

253
00:28:37.599 --> 00:28:39.582
       WHERE'S THE IMP ?

254
00:28:42.354 --> 00:28:44.388
Queen: WHERE IS OUR BROTHER ?

255
00:28:44.456 --> 00:28:46.389
GO AND FIND THE LITTLE BEAST.

256
00:28:48.594 --> 00:28:50.460
        TELL ME ABOUT JON ARRYN.

257
00:28:51.530 --> 00:28:54.865
ONE MINUTE HE WAS FINE
AND THEN...

258
00:28:54.934 --> 00:28:58.802
BURNED RIGHT THROUGH HIM.
WHATEVER IT WAS.

259
00:28:58.871 --> 00:29:00.904
I LOVED THAT MAN.

260
00:29:00.973 --> 00:29:02.355
                    WE BOTH DID.

261
00:29:02.441 --> 00:29:04.707
Robert:
HE NEVER HAD TO TEACH YOU MUCH.

262
00:29:04.776 --> 00:29:06.843
BUT ME ? YOU REMEMBER ME AT 16 ?

263
00:29:06.912 --> 00:29:08.778
                      (Chuckles)
ALL I WANTED TO DO

264
00:29:08.847 --> 00:29:11.548
WAS CRACK SKULLS AND FUCK GIRLS.

265
00:29:11.616 --> 00:29:14.818
HE SHOWED ME WHAT WAS WHAT.
                            AYE.

266
00:29:14.886 --> 00:29:17.554
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT.
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT
I DIDN'T LISTEN.

267
00:29:17.622 --> 00:29:19.339
          (Both laugh)

268
00:29:20.209 --> 00:29:21.942
(Sighs)

269
00:29:22.010 --> 00:29:25.445
I NEED YOU. NED.
DOWN AT KING'S LANDING.

270
00:29:25.513 --> 00:29:27.797
NOT UP HERE WHERE YOU'RE
NO DAMN USE TO ANYBODY.

271
00:29:29.768 --> 00:29:32.435
LORD EDDARD STARK...

272
00:29:32.504 --> 00:29:35.221
I WOULD NAME YOU
THE HAND OF THE KING.

273
00:29:39.445 --> 00:29:41.611
                  I'M NOT WORTHY
                  OF THE HONOR.

274
00:29:41.680 --> 00:29:43.129
I'M NOT TRYING
TO HONOR YOU.

275
00:29:43.198 --> 00:29:44.997
I'M TRYING TO GET YOU
TO RUN MY KINGDOM

276
00:29:45.066 --> 00:29:48.835
WHILE I EAT. DRINK AND WHORE
MY WAY TO AN EARLY GRAVE.

277
00:29:48.903 --> 00:29:51.038
DAMN IT. NED. STAND UP.

278
00:29:52.274 --> 00:29:54.274
YOU HELPED ME WIN
THE IRON THRONE.

279
00:29:54.343 --> 00:29:57.110
NOW HELP ME KEEP THE DAMN THING.

280
00:29:57.178 --> 00:29:59.613
WE WERE MEANT TO RULE TOGETHER.

281
00:29:59.681 --> 00:30:04.418
IF YOUR SISTER HAD LIVED.
WE'D HAVE BEEN BOUND BY BLOOD.

282
00:30:04.486 --> 00:30:06.520
WELL. IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

283
00:30:07.756 --> 00:30:11.174
I HAVE A SON.
YOU HAVE A DAUGHTER.

284
00:30:11.227 --> 00:30:13.577
WE'LL JOIN OUR HOUSES.

285
00:30:17.232 --> 00:30:19.799
        (Woman moaning)

286
00:30:30.796 --> 00:30:32.729
            (Sighs)

287
00:30:37.052 --> 00:30:38.017
          (Cup falls)

288
00:30:38.086 --> 00:30:39.385
        IT IS TRUE WHAT THEY SAY

289
00:30:39.455 --> 00:30:41.120
       ABOUT THE NORTHERN GIRLS.

290
00:30:41.189 --> 00:30:42.889
(Giggles)

291
00:30:49.281 --> 00:30:51.681
DID YOU HEAR
THE KING'S IN WINTERFELL ?

292
00:30:51.750 --> 00:30:53.450
            I DID HEAR SOMETHING
            ABOUT THAT.

293
00:30:53.519 --> 00:30:55.718
AND THE QUEEN
AND HER TWIN BROTHER.

294
00:30:55.787 --> 00:30:58.889
THEY SAY THAT HE IS
THE MOST HANDSOME MAN
IN THE SEVEN KINGDOMS.

295
00:30:58.957 --> 00:31:00.907
         AND THE OTHER BROTHER ?

296
00:31:00.976 --> 00:31:04.043
THE QUEEN HAS TWO BROTHERS ?
       THERE'S THE PRETTY ONE...

297
00:31:05.380 --> 00:31:08.315
     AND THERE'S THE CLEVER ONE.

298
00:31:08.383 --> 00:31:09.949
MMM...

299
00:31:10.018 --> 00:31:12.319
I HEAR THEY CALL HIM THE IMP.

300
00:31:12.387 --> 00:31:14.854
                 I HEAR HE HATES
                 THAT NICKNAME.

301
00:31:14.923 --> 00:31:17.757
OH ? I HEAR HE'S
MORE THAN EARNED IT.

302
00:31:17.826 --> 00:31:20.126
I HEAR HE'S
A DRUNKEN LITTLE LECHER.

303
00:31:20.195 --> 00:31:22.696
PRONE TO ALL MANNER
OF PERVERSIONS.

304
00:31:22.765 --> 00:31:25.098
                    CLEVER GIRL.

305
00:31:26.335 --> 00:31:29.453
WE'VE BEEN EXPECTING YOU.
LORD TYRION.

306
00:31:29.521 --> 00:31:31.154
                      HAVE YOU ?

307
00:31:31.223 --> 00:31:33.189
ALREADY ?
              OH !

308
00:31:35.494 --> 00:31:38.295
  THE GODS GAVE ME ONE BLESSING.
(Laughs)

309
00:31:38.347 --> 00:31:39.312
          (Door opens)

310
00:31:43.084 --> 00:31:45.652
         DON'T GET UP.
MY LORD.

311
00:31:45.721 --> 00:31:47.253
         SHOULD I EXPLAIN TO YOU
         THE MEANING

312
00:31:47.322 --> 00:31:49.472
      OF A CLOSED DOOR
      IN A WHOREHOUSE. BROTHER ?

313
00:31:49.541 --> 00:31:51.608
   YOU HAVE MUCH TO TEACH ME.
   NO DOUBT.

314
00:31:51.676 --> 00:31:55.495
     BUT OUR SISTER
     CRAVES YOUR ATTENTION.

315
00:31:55.564 --> 00:31:57.614
           SHE HAS ODD CRAVINGS.
           OUR SISTER.

316
00:31:57.682 --> 00:31:59.766
        A FAMILY TRAIT.

317
00:31:59.835 --> 00:32:03.236
NOW. THE STARKS ARE FEASTING US
AT SUNDOWN.

318
00:32:03.305 --> 00:32:05.072
      DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE
      WITH THESE PEOPLE.

319
00:32:05.140 --> 00:32:07.356
          I'M SORRY. I'VE BEGUN
          THE FEAST A BIT EARLY.

320
00:32:07.425 --> 00:32:10.777
           AND THIS IS THE FIRST
           OF MANY COURSES.

321
00:32:10.846 --> 00:32:13.112
 I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT SAY THAT.

322
00:32:13.181 --> 00:32:15.882
BUT SINCE WE'RE SHORT ON TIME...

323
00:32:15.951 --> 00:32:17.317
        COME ON. GIRLS.

324
00:32:17.386 --> 00:32:19.202
           (Giggling)

325
00:32:23.241 --> 00:32:25.075
      SEE YOU AT SUNDOWN.

326
00:32:25.143 --> 00:32:27.193
        Tyrion: CLOSE THE DOOR !

327
00:32:39.641 --> 00:32:43.042
        DID YOU HAVE TO BURY HER
        IN A PLACE LIKE THIS ?

328
00:32:44.279 --> 00:32:46.546
             SHE SHOULD BE
             ON A HILL SOMEWHERE

329
00:32:46.632 --> 00:32:49.032
     WITH THE SUN AND THE CLOUDS
     ABOVE HER.

330
00:32:49.101 --> 00:32:51.183
SHE WAS MY SISTER.

331
00:32:51.253 --> 00:32:54.020
                   THIS IS WHERE
                   SHE BELONGS.

332
00:32:54.089 --> 00:32:56.089
     SHE BELONGED WITH ME.

333
00:33:01.864 --> 00:33:05.065
    IN MY DREAMS.
    I KILL HIM EVERY NIGHT.

334
00:33:06.652 --> 00:33:11.621
        IT'S DONE. YOUR GRACE.
        THE TARGARYENS ARE GONE.

335
00:33:14.143 --> 00:33:15.925
                NOT ALL OF THEM.

336
00:33:17.679 --> 00:33:19.712
         (Gull crying)

337
00:33:26.988 --> 00:33:28.555
        Man: DAENERYS !

338
00:33:32.110 --> 00:33:33.860
           DAENERYS.

339
00:33:33.929 --> 00:33:36.012
    THERE'S OUR BRIDE-TO-BE.

340
00:33:36.948 --> 00:33:39.833
   LOOK. A GIFT FROM ILLYRIO.

341
00:33:41.135 --> 00:33:42.785
TOUCH IT.

342
00:33:42.855 --> 00:33:45.088
GO ON. FEEL THE FABRIC.

343
00:33:49.962 --> 00:33:51.828
MMM.

344
00:33:53.148 --> 00:33:55.281
ISN'T HE A GRACIOUS HOST ?

345
00:33:58.370 --> 00:34:00.036
     WE'VE BEEN HIS GUESTS
     FOR OVER A YEAR

346
00:34:00.105 --> 00:34:02.088
     AND HE'S NEVER
     ASKED US FOR ANYTHING.

347
00:34:02.157 --> 00:34:04.074
ILLYRIO'S NO FOOL.

348
00:34:04.142 --> 00:34:06.076
HE KNOWS I WON'T FORGET
MY FRIENDS

349
00:34:06.144 --> 00:34:08.261
WHEN I COME INTO MY THRONE.

350
00:34:12.684 --> 00:34:14.183
YOU STILL SLOUCH.

351
00:34:18.773 --> 00:34:20.990
LET THEM SEE.

352
00:34:23.896 --> 00:34:26.512
YOU HAVE A WOMAN'S BODY NOW.

353
00:34:29.601 --> 00:34:31.134
(Sighs)

354
00:34:44.499 --> 00:34:46.833
I NEED YOU
TO BE PERFECT TODAY.

355
00:34:49.070 --> 00:34:50.871
CAN YOU DO THAT FOR ME ?

356
00:34:53.976 --> 00:34:56.493
YOU DON'T WANT TO WAKE
THE DRAGON. DO YOU ?

357
00:34:58.563 --> 00:35:00.430
              NO.

358
00:35:06.688 --> 00:35:09.556
WHEN THEY WRITE THE HISTORY
OF MY REIGN. SWEET SISTER.

359
00:35:09.624 --> 00:35:11.824
THEY WILL SAY IT BEGAN TODAY.

360
00:35:35.117 --> 00:35:37.316
IT'S TOO HOT. MY LADY.

361
00:35:47.862 --> 00:35:49.462
         (Gulls crying)

362
00:35:58.056 --> 00:36:00.006
WHERE IS HE ?

363
00:36:00.075 --> 00:36:03.209
      THE DOTHRAKI ARE NOT KNOWN
      FOR THEIR PUNCTUALITY.

364
00:36:16.308 --> 00:36:20.393
 Illyrio: ATHCHOMAR CHOMAKAAN.
 KHAL VEZHVEN.

365
00:36:20.462 --> 00:36:22.462
             MAY I PRESENT
             MY HONORED GUESTS ?

366
00:36:22.548 --> 00:36:26.115
  VISERYS OF HOUSE TARGARYEN.

367
00:36:26.184 --> 00:36:27.717
     THE THIRD OF HIS NAME.

368
00:36:27.785 --> 00:36:31.254
THE RIGHTFUL KING OF THE ANDALS
AND THE FIRST MEN.

369
00:36:31.323 --> 00:36:32.639
        AND HIS SISTER.

370
00:36:32.707 --> 00:36:35.441
  DAENERYS OF HOUSE TARGARYEN.

371
00:36:36.678 --> 00:36:38.544
(Speaking Dothraki)

372
00:36:38.614 --> 00:36:41.130
DO YOU SEE HOW LONG
HIS HAIR IS ?

373
00:36:41.200 --> 00:36:44.033
WHEN DOTHRAKI
ARE DEFEATED IN COMBAT

374
00:36:44.102 --> 00:36:47.737
THEY CUT OFF THEIR BRAID SO THE
WHOLE WORLD CAN SEE THEIR SHAME.

375
00:36:47.806 --> 00:36:51.591
KHAL DROGO HAS NEVER
BEEN DEFEATED.

376
00:36:53.094 --> 00:36:54.477
HE'S A SAVAGE. OF COURSE.

377
00:36:54.546 --> 00:36:58.314
BUT HE'S ONE OF THE FINEST
KILLERS ALIVE.

378
00:36:58.383 --> 00:37:01.217
AND YOU WILL BE HIS QUEEN.

379
00:37:01.286 --> 00:37:03.086
          COME FORWARD. MY DEAR.

380
00:37:43.295 --> 00:37:44.494
      WHERE IS HE GOING ?

381
00:37:44.562 --> 00:37:45.995
           THE CEREMONY IS OVER.

382
00:37:46.063 --> 00:37:47.297
     BUT HE--BUT HE DIDN'T
     SAY ANYTHING.

383
00:37:47.365 --> 00:37:48.547
       DID HE LIKE HER ?

384
00:37:48.634 --> 00:37:50.100
           TRUST ME. YOUR GRACE.

385
00:37:50.168 --> 00:37:53.219
          IF HE DIDN'T LIKE HER.
          WE'D KNOW.

386
00:37:55.490 --> 00:37:57.790
 Illyrio: IT WON'T BE LONG NOW.

387
00:37:57.859 --> 00:37:59.659
SOON YOU WILL CROSS
THE NARROW SEA

388
00:37:59.728 --> 00:38:02.695
AND TAKE BACK
YOUR FATHER'S THRONE.

389
00:38:02.764 --> 00:38:06.666
THE PEOPLE DRINK SECRET TOASTS
TO YOUR HEALTH.

390
00:38:06.735 --> 00:38:09.469
THEY CRY OUT
FOR THEIR TRUE KING.

391
00:38:12.707 --> 00:38:14.674
  WHEN WILL THEY BE MARRIED ?

392
00:38:14.742 --> 00:38:18.311
        SOON. THE DOTHRAKI NEVER
        STAY STILL FOR LONG.

393
00:38:18.380 --> 00:38:21.314
IS IT TRUE THEY LIE
WITH THEIR HORSES ?

394
00:38:21.383 --> 00:38:23.749
      I WOULDN'T ASK KHAL DROGO.

395
00:38:23.818 --> 00:38:26.018
DO YOU TAKE ME FOR A FOOL ?

396
00:38:26.088 --> 00:38:27.853
          I TAKE YOU FOR A KING.

397
00:38:27.922 --> 00:38:31.091
          KINGS LACK THE CAUTION
          OF COMMON MEN.

398
00:38:31.159 --> 00:38:32.925
          MY APOLOGIES
          IF I'VE GIVEN OFFENSE.

399
00:38:32.994 --> 00:38:35.628
I KNOW HOW TO PLAY A MAN
LIKE DROGO.

400
00:38:35.697 --> 00:38:39.349
I GIVE HIM A QUEEN
AND HE GIVES ME AN ARMY.

401
00:38:39.417 --> 00:38:41.450
   I DON'T WANT TO BE HIS QUEEN.

402
00:38:46.558 --> 00:38:47.857
              I WANT TO GO HOME.

403
00:38:48.693 --> 00:38:51.027
            SO DO I.

404
00:38:51.096 --> 00:38:53.463
   I WANT US BOTH TO GO HOME.

405
00:38:53.531 --> 00:38:55.798
   BUT THEY TOOK IT FROM US.

406
00:38:55.867 --> 00:38:57.700
SO TELL ME. SWEET SISTER.

407
00:38:57.769 --> 00:38:59.536
HOW DO WE GO HOME ?

408
00:39:02.174 --> 00:39:03.372
                   I DON'T KNOW.

409
00:39:03.425 --> 00:39:05.792
WE GO HOME WITH AN ARMY.

410
00:39:07.812 --> 00:39:10.046
WITH KHAL DROGO'S ARMY.

411
00:39:11.265 --> 00:39:14.333
I WOULD LET HIS WHOLE TRIBE
FUCK YOU.

412
00:39:14.402 --> 00:39:17.636
ALL 40.000 MEN
AND THEIR HORSES TOO.

413
00:39:17.705 --> 00:39:19.255
IF THAT'S WHAT IT TOOK.

414
00:39:26.664 --> 00:39:27.830
            (Kisses)

415
00:39:36.608 --> 00:39:39.175
DO YOU THINK JOFFREY
WILL LIKE ME ?

416
00:39:39.243 --> 00:39:41.510
WHAT IF HE THINKS I'M UGLY ?

417
00:39:41.580 --> 00:39:45.214
THEN HE IS THE STUPIDEST PRINCE
THAT EVER LIVED.

418
00:39:47.685 --> 00:39:50.119
       HE'S SO HANDSOME.

419
00:39:50.188 --> 00:39:52.905
 WHEN WOULD WE BE MARRIED ?
 SOON ? OR DO WE HAVE TO WAIT ?

420
00:39:52.974 --> 00:39:56.142
HUSH NOW. YOUR FATHER
HASN'T EVEN SAID YES.

421
00:39:56.210 --> 00:39:57.960
     WHY WOULD HE SAY NO ?

422
00:39:58.013 --> 00:40:01.414
HE'D BE THE SECOND MOST POWERFUL
MAN IN THE KINGDOMS.

423
00:40:01.483 --> 00:40:04.333
HE'D HAVE TO LEAVE HOME.

424
00:40:04.403 --> 00:40:06.135
HE'D HAVE TO LEAVE ME.

425
00:40:07.755 --> 00:40:09.923
AND SO WOULD YOU.

426
00:40:09.991 --> 00:40:12.391
       YOU LEFT YOUR HOME
       TO COME HERE.

427
00:40:12.460 --> 00:40:14.593
   AND I'D BE QUEEN SOMEDAY.

428
00:40:16.214 --> 00:40:17.780
  PLEASE MAKE FATHER SAY YES !

429
00:40:17.849 --> 00:40:19.715
SANSA--
        PLEASE. PLEASE !

430
00:40:19.784 --> 00:40:22.568
      IT'S THE ONLY THING
      I EVER WANTED.

431
00:40:26.758 --> 00:40:28.991
       (Music playing.
       people chattering)

432
00:40:33.098 --> 00:40:34.780
           (Laughter)

433
00:40:36.535 --> 00:40:38.751
     FILL THAT UP !
     BOYS. RODRIK. COME ON.

434
00:40:38.819 --> 00:40:40.920
           COME ON !

435
00:40:40.989 --> 00:40:43.840
 COME HERE. YOU LITTLE BEAUTY !

436
00:40:43.908 --> 00:40:45.541
       (Robert laughing)

437
00:40:59.557 --> 00:41:01.473
        IS HE DEAD YET ?

438
00:41:06.331 --> 00:41:08.565
         UNCLE BENJEN.

439
00:41:08.633 --> 00:41:10.349
            (Laughs)

440
00:41:10.418 --> 00:41:12.234
        YOU GOT BIGGER.

441
00:41:13.004 --> 00:41:14.637
RODE ALL DAY.

442
00:41:14.706 --> 00:41:17.373
 DIDN'T WANT TO LEAVE YOU ALONE
 WITH THE LANNISTERS.

443
00:41:17.441 --> 00:41:18.791
 WHY AREN'T YOU AT THE FEAST ?

444
00:41:18.859 --> 00:41:21.660
     LADY STARK THOUGHT IT MIGHT
     INSULT THE ROYAL FAMILY

445
00:41:21.729 --> 00:41:24.430
               TO SEAT A BASTARD
               IN THEIR MIDST.

446
00:41:24.498 --> 00:41:26.949
WELL. YOU'RE ALWAYS
WELCOME ON THE WALL.

447
00:41:27.018 --> 00:41:29.051
NO BASTARD WAS EVER
REFUSED A SEAT THERE.

448
00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:30.854
             SO TAKE ME WITH YOU
             WHEN YOU GO BACK.

449
00:41:30.922 --> 00:41:33.856
JON--
              FATHER WILL LET ME
              IF YOU ASK HIM.

450
00:41:33.925 --> 00:41:35.608
                 I KNOW HE WILL.

451
00:41:38.446 --> 00:41:40.896
THE WALL ISN'T
GOING ANYWHERE.

452
00:41:40.965 --> 00:41:43.382
   I'M READY TO SWEAR YOUR OATH.

453
00:41:43.451 --> 00:41:46.618
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'D BE GIVING UP.

454
00:41:46.687 --> 00:41:48.671
WE HAVE NO FAMILIES.

455
00:41:48.740 --> 00:41:52.508
NONE OF US WILL EVER
FATHER SONS.
        I DON'T CARE ABOUT THAT.

456
00:41:52.577 --> 00:41:55.461
YOU MIGHT.
IF YOU KNEW WHAT IT MEANT.

457
00:41:58.916 --> 00:42:01.451
 (Sighs) I'D BETTER GET INSIDE.

458
00:42:01.519 --> 00:42:03.886
       RESCUE YOUR FATHER
       FROM HIS GUESTS.

459
00:42:06.858 --> 00:42:08.391
WE'LL TALK LATER.

460
00:42:17.301 --> 00:42:19.301
           Tyrion: YOUR UNCLE'S
           IN THE NIGHT'S WATCH.

461
00:42:22.607 --> 00:42:25.007
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
BACK THERE ?

462
00:42:25.076 --> 00:42:27.744
           PREPARING FOR A NIGHT
           WITH YOUR FAMILY.

463
00:42:32.516 --> 00:42:34.483
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO SEE THE WALL.

464
00:42:34.552 --> 00:42:36.385
        YOU'RE TYRION LANNISTER.

465
00:42:36.454 --> 00:42:38.037
           THE QUEEN'S BROTHER ?

466
00:42:38.106 --> 00:42:41.273
MY GREATEST ACCOMPLISHMENT.

467
00:42:41.342 --> 00:42:44.310
AND YOU. YOU'RE NED STARK'S
BASTARD. AREN'T YOU ?

468
00:42:47.465 --> 00:42:49.515
DID I OFFEND YOU ? SORRY.

469
00:42:51.770 --> 00:42:54.103
YOU ARE THE BASTARD. THOUGH.

470
00:42:55.539 --> 00:42:57.740
               LORD EDDARD STARK
               IS MY FATHER.

471
00:42:59.110 --> 00:43:01.811
AND LADY STARK
IS NOT YOUR MOTHER.

472
00:43:01.880 --> 00:43:04.796
MAKING YOU...THE BASTARD.

473
00:43:06.334 --> 00:43:08.901
LET ME GIVE YOU
SOME ADVICE. BASTARD.

474
00:43:10.138 --> 00:43:12.004
NEVER FORGET WHAT YOU ARE.

475
00:43:12.073 --> 00:43:14.440
THE REST OF THE WORLD WILL NOT.

476
00:43:14.509 --> 00:43:16.842
WEAR IT LIKE ARMOR...

477
00:43:16.911 --> 00:43:18.894
AND IT CAN NEVER BE USED
TO HURT YOU.

478
00:43:20.865 --> 00:43:23.532
       WHAT THE HELL DO YOU KNOW
       ABOUT BEING A BASTARD ?

479
00:43:26.004 --> 00:43:29.188
ALL DWARVES ARE BASTARDS
IN THEIR FATHER'S EYES.

480
00:43:44.155 --> 00:43:45.754
  (Music playing. chattering)

481
00:43:45.824 --> 00:43:47.423
           (Laughter)

482
00:43:50.161 --> 00:43:52.662
               YOU AT A FEAST...

483
00:43:52.730 --> 00:43:54.697
     IT'S LIKE A BEAR IN A TRAP.

484
00:43:56.400 --> 00:43:59.268
THE BOY I BEHEADED...

485
00:43:59.336 --> 00:44:02.171
DID YOU KNOW HIM ?
    OF COURSE I DID. JUST A LAD.

486
00:44:03.441 --> 00:44:05.574
          BUT HE WAS TOUGH. NED.

487
00:44:05.643 --> 00:44:06.942
                  A TRUE RANGER.

488
00:44:07.011 --> 00:44:08.911
(Scoffs)

489
00:44:08.979 --> 00:44:11.513
HE WAS TALKING MADNESS.

490
00:44:11.582 --> 00:44:13.566
SAID THE WALKERS
SLAUGHTERED HIS FRIENDS.

491
00:44:13.634 --> 00:44:17.353
             THE TWO HE WAS WITH
             ARE STILL MISSING.

492
00:44:17.422 --> 00:44:20.973
HMPH. A WILDLING AMBUSH.

493
00:44:21.876 --> 00:44:24.227
                          MAYBE.

494
00:44:24.295 --> 00:44:26.896
   DIREWOLVES SOUTH OF THE WALL.

495
00:44:26.964 --> 00:44:29.198
            TALK OF THE WALKERS.

496
00:44:29.267 --> 00:44:32.968
      AND MY BROTHER MIGHT BE
      THE NEXT HAND OF THE KING.

497
00:44:33.038 --> 00:44:34.787
               WINTER IS COMING.

498
00:44:36.490 --> 00:44:38.324
WINTER IS COMING.

499
00:44:38.393 --> 00:44:39.875
         (They chuckle)

500
00:44:39.944 --> 00:44:42.828
UNCLE BENJEN.
         ROBB BOY.

501
00:44:42.897 --> 00:44:44.464
                   HOW ARE YOU ?
           I'M GOOD.

502
00:44:44.549 --> 00:44:46.249
           (Laughter)

503
00:44:47.835 --> 00:44:50.636
IS THIS YOUR FIRST TIME
IN THE NORTH. YOUR GRACE ?

504
00:44:50.705 --> 00:44:53.339
            YES. LOVELY COUNTRY.

505
00:44:57.244 --> 00:45:00.480
I'M SURE IT'S VERY GRIM
AFTER KING'S LANDING.

506
00:45:01.900 --> 00:45:04.467
I REMEMBER HOW SCARED I WAS
WHEN NED BROUGHT ME UP HERE

507
00:45:04.535 --> 00:45:06.151
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

508
00:45:08.456 --> 00:45:09.955
             HELLO. LITTLE DOVE.

509
00:45:11.058 --> 00:45:13.292
           BUT YOU ARE A BEAUTY.

510
00:45:13.361 --> 00:45:15.711
               HOW OLD ARE YOU ?
     THIRTEEN. YOUR GRACE.

511
00:45:15.780 --> 00:45:18.430
                 YOU'RE TALL.
                 STILL GROWING ?

512
00:45:18.499 --> 00:45:20.366
    I THINK SO. YOUR GRACE.

513
00:45:20.434 --> 00:45:22.501
AND HAVE YOU BLED YET ?

514
00:45:27.708 --> 00:45:29.091
        NO. YOUR GRACE.

515
00:45:30.695 --> 00:45:34.030
YOUR DRESS. DID YOU MAKE IT ?

516
00:45:34.098 --> 00:45:37.249
SUCH TALENT.
YOU MUST MAKE SOMETHING FOR ME.

517
00:45:39.737 --> 00:45:43.255
           I HEAR WE MIGHT SHARE
           A GRANDCHILD SOMEDAY.

518
00:45:43.324 --> 00:45:44.573
I HEAR THE SAME.

519
00:45:44.642 --> 00:45:47.260
      YOUR DAUGHTER WILL DO WELL
      IN THE CAPITAL.

520
00:45:47.328 --> 00:45:50.579
    SUCH A BEAUTY SHOULDN'T STAY
    HIDDEN UP HERE FOREVER.

521
00:46:07.332 --> 00:46:10.016
YOUR PARDON.
              I HEAR WE MIGHT BE
              NEIGHBORS SOON.

522
00:46:10.084 --> 00:46:11.383
               I HOPE IT'S TRUE.

523
00:46:11.452 --> 00:46:13.586
YES. THE KING HAS HONORED ME
WITH HIS OFFER.

524
00:46:13.655 --> 00:46:17.556
I'M SURE WE'LL HAVE A TOURNAMENT
TO CELEBRATE YOUR NEW TITLE.
IF YOU ACCEPT.

525
00:46:17.625 --> 00:46:19.157
       IT WOULD BE GOOD
       TO HAVE YOU ON THE FIELD.

526
00:46:19.226 --> 00:46:21.644
      THE COMPETITION HAS BECOME
      A BIT STALE.

527
00:46:21.712 --> 00:46:24.046
I DON'T FIGHT IN TOURNAMENTS.
                            NO ?

528
00:46:24.115 --> 00:46:25.731
   GETTING A LITTLE OLD FOR IT ?

529
00:46:25.817 --> 00:46:27.549
(Chuckles)

530
00:46:27.618 --> 00:46:29.718
I DON'T FIGHT IN TOURNAMENTS

531
00:46:29.787 --> 00:46:32.221
BECAUSE WHEN I FIGHT A MAN
FOR REAL.

532
00:46:32.290 --> 00:46:34.941
I DON'T WANT HIM TO KNOW
WHAT I CAN DO.

533
00:46:36.310 --> 00:46:37.543
                      WELL SAID.

534
00:46:39.046 --> 00:46:41.079
           (Laughing)
                          ARYA !

535
00:46:42.766 --> 00:46:44.483
                IT'S NOT FUNNY !

536
00:46:44.552 --> 00:46:47.252
           SHE ALWAYS DOES THIS.

537
00:46:47.338 --> 00:46:49.805
      THIS WAS MY FAVORITE DRESS
      AND SHE RUINED IT.

538
00:46:49.874 --> 00:46:52.391
            SHE ALWAYS DOES IT
            AND IT'S NOT FUNNY !

539
00:46:52.460 --> 00:46:54.359
      Robb: TIME FOR BED.

540
00:46:55.797 --> 00:46:57.563
         (Arya groans)

541
00:47:05.372 --> 00:47:07.105
Ned: I'M A NORTHMAN.

542
00:47:08.743 --> 00:47:10.876
I BELONG HERE WITH YOU.
NOT DOWN SOUTH

543
00:47:10.945 --> 00:47:13.312
IN THAT RATS' NEST
THEY CALL A CAPITAL.

544
00:47:14.315 --> 00:47:17.049
        I WON'T LET HIM
        TAKE YOU.

545
00:47:18.619 --> 00:47:21.253
THE KING TAKES
WHAT HE WANTS.

546
00:47:21.322 --> 00:47:23.656
(Snorts)
THAT'S WHY HE'S KING.

547
00:47:24.659 --> 00:47:28.360
    I'LL SAY. "LISTEN. FAT MAN."

548
00:47:28.429 --> 00:47:29.562
(Laughs)

549
00:47:29.630 --> 00:47:32.798
      "YOU ARE NOT TAKING
      MY HUSBAND ANYWHERE.

550
00:47:32.867 --> 00:47:34.967
    "HE BELONGS TO ME NOW."

551
00:47:38.539 --> 00:47:40.639
HOW DID HE GET SO FAT ?

552
00:47:40.708 --> 00:47:45.043
  HE ONLY STOPS EATING WHEN IT'S
  TIME FOR A DRINK. (Chuckles)

553
00:47:45.112 --> 00:47:46.579
           (Knocking)

554
00:47:46.647 --> 00:47:49.448
    Man: IT'S MAESTER LUWIN.
    MY LORD.

555
00:47:50.518 --> 00:47:52.351
SEND HIM IN.

556
00:47:54.722 --> 00:47:57.756
                PARDON. MY LORD.
                MY LADY.

557
00:47:57.825 --> 00:47:59.725
         A RIDER IN THE NIGHT...

558
00:47:59.794 --> 00:48:01.960
               FROM YOUR SISTER.

559
00:48:09.721 --> 00:48:12.387
STAY.
   THIS WAS SENT FROM THE EYRIE.

560
00:48:12.456 --> 00:48:14.239
         (Door closes)

561
00:48:18.312 --> 00:48:20.646
        WHAT'S SHE DOING
        AT THE EYRIE ?

562
00:48:20.715 --> 00:48:23.649
   SHE HASN'T BEEN BACK THERE
   SINCE HER WEDDING.

563
00:48:31.725 --> 00:48:33.526
        Ned: WHAT NEWS ?

564
00:48:35.229 --> 00:48:37.196
Catelyn: SHE'S FLED THE CAPITAL.

565
00:48:40.050 --> 00:48:42.618
              SHE SAYS JON ARRYN
              WAS MURDERED.

566
00:48:42.686 --> 00:48:44.669
              BY THE LANNISTERS.

567
00:48:44.756 --> 00:48:47.423
               SHE SAYS THE KING
               IS IN DANGER.

568
00:48:47.492 --> 00:48:49.774
SHE'S FRESH WIDOWED. CAT.

569
00:48:49.843 --> 00:48:51.560
SHE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT SHE'S SAYING.

570
00:48:51.628 --> 00:48:54.263
            LYSA'S HEAD WOULD BE
            ON A SPIKE RIGHT NOW

571
00:48:54.332 --> 00:48:56.966
          IF THE WRONG PEOPLE
          HAD FOUND THAT LETTER.

572
00:48:57.034 --> 00:48:59.251
          DO YOU THINK SHE WOULD
          RISK HER LIFE.

573
00:48:59.320 --> 00:49:00.970
                 HER SON'S LIFE.

574
00:49:01.022 --> 00:49:04.223
      IF SHE WASN'T CERTAIN
      HER HUSBAND WAS MURDERED ?

575
00:49:11.632 --> 00:49:13.566
         IF THIS NEWS IS TRUE...

576
00:49:13.634 --> 00:49:17.236
     AND THE LANNISTERS CONSPIRE
     AGAINST THE THRONE.

577
00:49:17.305 --> 00:49:19.771
          WHO BUT YOU
          CAN PROTECT THE KING ?

578
00:49:19.840 --> 00:49:22.140
THEY MURDERED
THE LAST HAND.

579
00:49:22.210 --> 00:49:24.476
NOW YOU WANT NED
TO TAKE THE JOB ?

580
00:49:24.545 --> 00:49:28.647
              THE KING RODE FOR
              A MONTH TO ASK FOR
              LORD STARK'S HELP.

581
00:49:28.716 --> 00:49:31.083
               HE'S THE ONLY ONE
               HE TRUSTS.

582
00:49:32.553 --> 00:49:35.454
              YOU SWORE THE KING
              AN OATH. MY LORD.

583
00:49:35.523 --> 00:49:39.191
HE'S SPENT HALF HIS LIFE
FIGHTING ROBERT'S WARS.

584
00:49:39.260 --> 00:49:41.176
      HE OWES HIM NOTHING.

585
00:49:43.181 --> 00:49:46.448
YOUR FATHER AND BROTHER
RODE SOUTH ONCE

586
00:49:46.517 --> 00:49:48.650
ON A KING'S DEMAND.

587
00:49:51.055 --> 00:49:52.888
               A DIFFERENT TIME.

588
00:49:54.558 --> 00:49:56.292
               A DIFFERENT KING.

589
00:50:00.031 --> 00:50:02.097
(Noisy chatter)
(Drumming)

590
00:50:23.437 --> 00:50:25.370
           (Hissing)

591
00:50:30.611 --> 00:50:31.910
            (Gasps)

592
00:50:57.805 --> 00:50:59.638
             WHEN DO I MEET WITH
             THE KHAL ?

593
00:50:59.707 --> 00:51:01.373
       WE NEED TO BEGIN PLANNING
       THE INVASION.

594
00:51:01.442 --> 00:51:04.960
  IF KHAL DROGO HAS PROMISED YOU
  A CROWN. YOU SHALL HAVE IT.

595
00:51:05.029 --> 00:51:09.131
             WHEN ?
     WHEN THEIR OMENS FAVOR WAR.

596
00:51:09.200 --> 00:51:11.766
I PISS ON DOTHRAKI OMENS.

597
00:51:11.835 --> 00:51:14.403
I'VE WAITED 17 YEARS
TO GET MY THRONE BACK.

598
00:51:23.865 --> 00:51:26.798
       (Crowd ululating)
(Grunting)

599
00:51:41.365 --> 00:51:42.564
           (Cheering)

600
00:51:52.310 --> 00:51:54.292
          ETAYO AKKA.

601
00:51:54.362 --> 00:51:55.728
         (Blades clang)

602
00:52:05.372 --> 00:52:07.389
           (Screams)

603
00:52:14.448 --> 00:52:17.149
      A DOTHRAKI WEDDING WITHOUT
      AT LEAST THREE DEATHS

604
00:52:17.218 --> 00:52:19.718
                  IS CONSIDERED
                  A DULL AFFAIR.

605
00:52:20.805 --> 00:52:22.637
           (Laughing)

606
00:52:32.183 --> 00:52:34.216
JADI. ZHEY JORAH ANDAHLI !

607
00:52:34.284 --> 00:52:35.818
         KHAL VEZHVEN.

608
00:52:41.792 --> 00:52:45.694
           A SMALL GIFT.
           FOR THE NEW KHALEESI.

609
00:52:45.763 --> 00:52:48.414
        SONGS AND HISTORIES
        FROM THE SEVEN KINGDOMS.

610
00:52:50.017 --> 00:52:51.366
THANK YOU. SER.

611
00:52:53.171 --> 00:52:55.905
ARE YOU FROM MY COUNTRY ?

612
00:52:55.957 --> 00:52:58.057
               SER JORAH MORMONT
               OF BEAR ISLAND.

613
00:52:58.125 --> 00:53:00.859
            I SERVED YOUR FATHER
            FOR MANY YEARS.

614
00:53:00.928 --> 00:53:04.663
 GODS BE GOOD. I HOPE TO
 ALWAYS SERVE THE RIGHTFUL KING.

615
00:53:27.154 --> 00:53:29.872
        DRAGON'S EGGS. DAENERYS.

616
00:53:29.941 --> 00:53:32.724
           FROM THE SHADOW LANDS
           BEYOND ASSHAI.

617
00:53:32.793 --> 00:53:35.811
           THE AGES HAVE
           TURNED THEM TO STONE.

618
00:53:35.880 --> 00:53:37.746
         BUT THEY WILL ALWAYS BE
         BEAUTIFUL.

619
00:53:40.084 --> 00:53:42.050
THANK YOU. MAGISTER.

620
00:54:50.437 --> 00:54:52.370
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

621
00:54:56.710 --> 00:54:58.043
         SER JORAH. I--

622
00:54:58.112 --> 00:55:00.929
    I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SAY
    "THANK YOU" IN DOTHRAKI.

623
00:55:00.998 --> 00:55:03.732
THERE IS NO WORD
FOR "THANK YOU" IN DOTHRAKI.

624
00:55:24.989 --> 00:55:26.622
        MAKE HIM HAPPY.

625
00:55:39.453 --> 00:55:41.353
        (Waves crashing)

626
00:56:26.300 --> 00:56:28.249
              NO.
(Sobs)

627
00:56:31.689 --> 00:56:34.422
      DO YOU KNOW
      THE COMMON TONGUE ?

628
00:56:38.312 --> 00:56:39.978
          (Pin clanks)
                             NO.

629
00:56:44.301 --> 00:56:47.936
     IS "NO" THE ONLY WORD
     THAT YOU KNOW ?

630
00:56:48.005 --> 00:56:49.220
                             NO.

631
00:56:54.962 --> 00:56:56.879
      (Continues sobbing)

632
00:57:17.718 --> 00:57:19.784
              ROUGH NIGHT. IMP ?

633
00:57:19.853 --> 00:57:21.886
     IF I GET THROUGH THIS
     WITHOUT SQUIRTING

634
00:57:21.955 --> 00:57:24.889
   FROM ONE END OR THE OTHER.
   IT'LL BE A MIRACLE.

635
00:57:24.958 --> 00:57:26.791
               I DIDN'T PICK YOU
               FOR A HUNTER.

636
00:57:26.860 --> 00:57:30.995
   THE GREATEST IN THE LAND--
   MY SPEAR NEVER MISSES.

637
00:57:31.064 --> 00:57:33.532
              IT'S NOT HUNTING
              IF YOU PAY FOR IT.

638
00:57:42.042 --> 00:57:44.192
    ARE YOU AS GOOD WITH A SPEAR
    AS YOU USED TO BE ?

639
00:57:44.245 --> 00:57:46.745
NO. BUT I'M STILL
BETTER THAN YOU.

640
00:57:46.831 --> 00:57:49.631
                        (Laughs)

641
00:57:49.700 --> 00:57:51.533
            I KNOW WHAT I'M
            PUTTING YOU THROUGH.

642
00:57:51.601 --> 00:57:53.468
       THANK YOU FOR SAYING YES.

643
00:57:55.222 --> 00:57:58.690
             I ONLY ASK YOU
             BECAUSE I NEED YOU.

644
00:57:58.759 --> 00:58:02.311
          YOU'RE A LOYAL FRIEND.
          YOU HEAR ME ?

645
00:58:02.379 --> 00:58:04.029
                 A LOYAL FRIEND.

646
00:58:04.098 --> 00:58:05.696
          THE LAST ONE I'VE GOT.

647
00:58:07.518 --> 00:58:10.919
I HOPE I'LL SERVE YOU WELL.
                       YOU WILL.

648
00:58:10.988 --> 00:58:15.440
          AND I'LL MAKE SURE YOU
          DON'T LOOK SO FUCKING
          GRIM ALL THE TIME.

649
00:58:15.508 --> 00:58:18.393
COME ON. BOYS.
LET'S GO KILL SOME BOAR !

650
00:58:27.988 --> 00:58:29.421
         COME ON. YOU.

651
00:58:44.555 --> 00:58:45.921
            (Whines)

652
00:58:54.782 --> 00:58:56.297
            (Grunts)

653
00:59:00.321 --> 00:59:02.070
         (Barks softly)

654
00:59:08.662 --> 00:59:10.495
        (Woman gasping)

655
00:59:14.585 --> 00:59:16.151
        (Woman moaning)

656
00:59:26.313 --> 00:59:29.080
      (Grunting. moaning)

657
00:59:44.264 --> 00:59:45.797
(Gasps)

658
00:59:45.866 --> 00:59:48.549
STOP ! STOP.
            (Gasps)

659
00:59:53.523 --> 00:59:55.840
ARE YOU COMPLETELY MAD ?

660
00:59:55.909 --> 00:59:58.493
           HE SAW US.
IT'S ALL RIGHT. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

661
00:59:58.562 --> 01:00:00.645
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
          HE SAW US !

662
01:00:00.714 --> 01:00:02.713
I HEARD YOU THE FIRST TIME.

663
01:00:04.018 --> 01:00:05.533
           (Whimpers)

664
01:00:07.604 --> 01:00:10.454
QUITE THE LITTLE CLIMBER.
AREN'T YOU ?

665
01:00:10.524 --> 01:00:13.407
HOW OLD ARE YOU. BOY ?
                            TEN.

666
01:00:13.477 --> 01:00:14.942
TEN.

667
01:00:23.904 --> 01:00:26.154
THE THINGS I DO FOR LOVE.
            (Gasps)
